    <item>
      <title>4.4 Inverses of Combined Functions</title>
      <link>https://duragauge.github.io/chapter-4/4.4/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://duragauge.github.io/chapter-4/4.4/</guid>
      <description>&lt;div style=&#34;position:relative; clear:both; padding:0;&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;img src=&#34;https://duragauge.github.io/img/chapter-4/small-3871893_1280.jpg&#34;  title=&#34;Image by Vinson Tan from Pixabay &#34;  alt=&#34;Image by Vinson Tan from Pixabay &#34; style=&#34;display:block; width:100%; height:auto;&#34; &gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;span style=&#34;position:absolute; height:auto; bottom:0em; right:0em; margin:0;  padding: .1em .3em;  color:white;  font-size: .8em;  background:rgba(0, 0, 0, 1);  text-align:right;  z-index:5;  opacity:0.65;  border-radius:.3em 0em 0em 0em;&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;a href = &#34;https://pixabay.com/images/id-3871893/&#34;&gt;Image by Vinson Tan from Pixabay &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;br&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;introduction&#34;&gt;Introduction&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;In the 1980&#39;s Hasbro changed the toy world by introducing a line of robot action figures known as &lt;em&gt;Transformers&lt;/em&gt;.  What made each Transformer special was that if you bent the legs, twisted the torso, and folded the arms, the robot would change into something else, like a car or an airplane.  Undoing each of those steps in the reverse order would change it back into a robot again.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
